<p>The above command will return HTTP status code 200 on success</p>
</blockquote>

<p>Use this method to change the account options. You can enable or disable JS/CSS file minification. You can also enable/disable automatic fetching via HTTP or S3 from a remote location.</p>

<aside class="warning">Be carefull when changing account options.</aside>
<h3 id='http-request-2'>HTTP Request</h3>
<p>`
POST /v2/account HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer BEARER_TOKEN
Host: api.sirv.com</p>

<p>{
  &quot;fetching&quot;: {
    &quot;enabled&quot;: false,
    &quot;type&quot;: &quot;http&quot;,
    &quot;http&quot;: {
      &quot;url&quot;: &quot;https://mysite.com&quot;
    }
  },
  &quot;minify&quot;: {
    &quot;enabled&quot;: false
  },
  &quot;aliases&quot;: {
    &quot;test1&quot;: {
      &quot;prefix&quot;: &quot;/&quot;
    }
  }
}
`</p>
<h3 id='url-parameters'>URL Parameters</h3>
<p>None</p>
